track_notes:
CAUTION: Part of the activation zone for this summit is within tribal land which requires a permit to enter.  Be very aware of your position in relation to the activation zone and the tribal boundaries.

Start at the east Baldy trailhead and ascend to the activation zone.  Return to the trail junction and descend via the West Baldy trail.  We had 3 in our group and left one car at the West Baldy trailhead.  15.25 miles RT.

East Baldy Trail is the shortest leg and can be taken up and back 14 miles RT.  West Baldy trail is more scenic but both are beautiful.
track_title: Mount Baldy - East and West Baldy Trails - Loop
